The Hydraulic Co said itsboard approved a three-for-two stock split of its common stockand increased its quarterly cash dividend.    It said the stock split will occur through a 50 pct stockdistribution on Hydraulic's common stock, payable April 30 tostockholders of record on April 3.    The quarterly cash dividend, payable April 15 tostockholders of record on April 3, is to be paid on Hydraulic'spre-split shares that are currently outstanding, the companysaid.    The dividend will be 54.75 cts per share, up from 52 ctsper share.It will represent a quarterly common stock cashdividend of 36.50 cts per share on the share that will beoutstanding after the stock split, the company said. Reuter&#3;